# Notifications list (Meriter)

## Base typography

- **Card subtitle container** (`InfoCard`): `text-sm text-brand-text-secondary` on the wrapper around `subtitle` so body copy has one consistent size across notification types.
- **In-code tokens** (`NOTIFY_SUB` in `NotificationsClient.tsx`): keep subtitle JSX aligned with this rule.
  - **Stack**: `flex flex-col gap-1.5`
  - **Body**: `text-brand-text-primary whitespace-pre-wrap break-words`
  - **Muted / labels**: `text-brand-text-secondary whitespace-pre-wrap break-words`
  - **Navigable entities** (users, communities, projects, posts, “open post”): `font-medium text-brand-primary hover:underline break-words` on `Link`, with `onClick={(e) => e.stopPropagation()}` so row click still works.
  - **Entity plain text** (no URL): `font-medium text-brand-text-primary break-words`
  - **Timestamp** (`NOTIFY_SUB.stamp`): `text-xs text-base-content/55` (one step smaller than body)

Do not mix arbitrary `text-xs` / `text-sm` inside subtitle rows except the timestamp.

## Content layout

- **One logical unit per line** where it improves scanning: actor name, action line, post/ticket title, community or project name, optional comment/reason, then timestamp.
- **User names** that identify a profile: own line when paired with action suffixes; use `routes.userProfile(id)` (or existing helpers) when `id` is known.
- **Community / project / post titles**: separate lines when both title and place matter; link when `communityId`, `projectId`, or post route is available.
- **Prefer structured JSX branches** in `renderNotificationSubtitle` over a single translation string that concatenates names and titles.
- **`project_distributed`**: metadata `payoutBucket` is `founder` | `investor` | `team` (API / `project-payout.service.ts`). Subtitle maps unknown buckets to a trimmed fallback; known buckets use `notifications.projectDistributedSubtitleRole` with `{ role }` from `notifications.projectDistributedPayoutRoleFounder` | `...Investor` | `...Team` (see `renderNotificationSubtitle` for `project_distributed`) — do not show raw API bucket strings to users when a mapped label exists.
- **Fallback** (`formatNotificationMessage` + default subtitle): keep lines split by `\n`; actor row uses a profile link when `actor.id` is present.

## Files

- `web/src/app/meriter/notifications/NotificationsClient.tsx` — subtitle rendering and `NOTIFY_SUB`.
- `web/src/components/ui/InfoCard.tsx` — title `text-sm`, subtitle wrapper size as above.
